The article discusses a statement made by the White House Press Secretary regarding the importance of extending middle-class tax cuts for the economy. The President supports the House's decision to pass a permanent extension of these tax cuts. However, because Republicans are insisting on also extending tax cuts for the wealthy, the President has instructed Director Lew and Secretary Geithner to work with Congress to find a solution. The talks have recently started and are ongoing, but reports claiming that a deal is imminent are inaccurate and premature.